# Title file
# This file stores information on the titles used in the plots
#
# The top level is the type (corresponds to the type as listed in the plots_file.dat).
# If no type is selected in plots_file.dat then the default is 4up.
#
# The next level down is the plot letter followed by the top title and the subtitle (colon separated).
# The following strings are automatically replaced at run time for each plot:
#    field = the title in plots_file.dat. If this is missing then it uses the title in the item_file.dat
#    season = the season of the plot (DJF, MAM, JJA, SON or ANN)
#    control = the control suite-id and name (as listed in source_file.dat)
#    exper = the experiment suite-id and name (as listed in source_file.dat)
#    observations = the observations name (as listed in obs_file.dat)
#
# Optional extra switches are avalable here
#    layout = layout of the plots on the page XbyY where X is the number of plots
#             in the x direction and Y the number of plots on the y direction. If
#             omitted it keeps to a square layout 1by1, 2by2 or 3by3 depending on
#             the number of plots requested. Used to override settings for
#             location_dict, figsize and font_size in the define_page routine

start:1up
   a:field for season:  
end:

start:2up
   a:field for season:control
   b:field for season:exper
end:

start:3up
   a:field for season:control
   b:field for season:exper
   c:field for season:exper minus control
end:3up

